chairman of Honeywell, which is being acquired by Allied Signal,
talks about trying to meld together two companies and two corporate
cultures.
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET-WORKPLACE (Undated) _ In the Internet industry, for
both companies and individuals, pacing, in one way or another, has
become critical in a race that is becoming more a marathon and less
a sprint. As the Internet economy matures, high-technology
companies are expanding programs and policies intended to help
harried workers balance their personal lives and the demands of
work. A greater use of flexible hours, part-time work, day care,
sabbaticals and longer vacations are all part of that effort. By
Steve Lohr.
