<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-CLIPS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TAYLOR TAKES DAY OFF AS PRECAUTION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 c.1999 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Realizing the Los Angeles Clippers offense has
booked a six-month ride on his deltoids, Maurice Taylor decided to
spend Tuesday in the shop for minor maintenance.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can practice now and play now,'' said Taylor, whose bruised
left shoulder prevented him from participating in the Clippers'
latest workout, ``or sit out this practice and be ready to play
Nov. 2.''
</P>
<P>
   The shoulder injury occurred in Phoenix last week by an
inadvertent, returning -to-earth elbow from former teammate Rodney
Rogers.
</P>
<P>
   But evidence that the injury isn't serious was gathered last
weekend, when Taylor scored 45 points and had 20 rebounds in
exhibition victories over Vancouver and Seattle.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not too bad,'' said Taylor, who plans to play in
tonight's exhibition home-opener against the Milwaukee Bucks at
Staples Center. ``I wanted to make sure it (the shoulder) was
right.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Murdock-umentation: After missing the first four rehearsal
games with an ankle sprain, veteran point guard Eric Murdock made
his unofficial Clippers debut last weekend.
</P>
<P>
   ``He played well,'' coach Chris Ford said of Murdock, who
averaged 10 points in the two wins. ``He shot the ball well,
knocked down the open shots off the double-teams inside.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's a steady, consistent player.''
</P>
<P>
   Murdock, who was acquired from New Jersey in a deal that sent
Johnny Newman to the Nets, has welcomed the opportunity to join a
team offering a significant role.
</P>
<P>
   ``For me, everything was positive, basketball-wise,'' said
Murdock, who left Miami as a free agent for his home-state Nets
before last season. ``We've been playing well, working hard, and
that's the key. We dont' have a lot of experience, so we have to
work harder than the other team.''
</P>
<P>
   Leg injuries limited Murdock's experience to 15 games last
season, one year after his gig as caddy to Tim Hardaway in Miami.
But Murdock, 31, did average 14 points and more than six assists
over three full seasons in Milwaukee.
</P>
<P>
   __ Fast breaks: Because of a death in the family, Clippers sixth
man Tyrone Nesby will not be with the team for tonight's game. . .
. X-rays taken Monday on guard Eric Piatkowski's sore ribs (another
bit of pain gained in Phoenix) were negative. Piatkowski practiced
Tuesday and will play tonight.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
