   NUTS-RECIPES (Palm Beach Post) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   WINE-COLUMN _ Story about Mel Schlachter, the wine-making good
reverend of Troy, Ohio. (Fisher, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   GARY-COOPER _ WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Gary Cooper was the most
gravely beautiful of all male stars, with a moral power that made
him the supreme object of contemplation for directors as varied as
Frank Capra, Howard Hawks, Cecil B. DeMille and Fred Zinnemann.
Cooper was the quiet American _ strong and resolute, capable of
doubt, incapable of cruelty. It was the gentleness that set him
apart from actors such as John Wayne and James Stewart, who could
be aggressively harsh. In contrast to them, Cooper was solitary and
shy, with a terrible anxiety at the heart of his personality. As
described by his daughter and virtually everybody who ever crossed
his path, Cooper was an enchanting man, sweet, mild and
unpretentious. But he was also lugging something around with him,
something heavy _ he aged very quickly, was periodically troubled
by ulcers and other manifestations of a nervous disposition, and
died young, at 60. What was was eating him? (Eyman, Palm Beach
Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TV-GROSSADS _ Once taste was a word advertisers used to describe
their products, as in ``Tastes Great. Less Filling.'' But, these
days, taste _ or lack of it _ has taken on a broader meaning in the
TV ad biz. Words and images that a few years ago never would have
seen the light of America's living rooms are suddenly showing up in
sales pitches for all manner of products. (Scott, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET-WRESTLING1027
</P>
<P>
   The weekly CoxNet wrestling page is available Wednesday
afternoons by 5 p.m. Keying to the Monday wrestling events, It's
good for publication any day through Sunday. Here are the elements
on the page, which are also moving on the entertainment wire:
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-CHOCOLATE _ DAYTON, OHIO_ As rare sights go, this one
was as uncommon as seeing Halley's Comet pass overhead, Big Foot
standing out in the open or Montgomery County Recorder Joy Clark
sitting behind her desk. I saw Sexual Chocolate melt.Saw him shrink
from this mountainous masher right down into a ``yes ma'am'', ``no
ma'am'', ``please excuse me ma'am'' sweetheart. It happened in a
private dressing room just before a recent World Wrestling
Federation show in Dayton, Ohio. But to get the picture, you need
some history. Sexual Chocolate is the stage name of Mark Henry, the
380-pound former Olympic weightlifter turned WWF star. (Archdeacon,
Cox News Service) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
