<HEADLINE>
JAMAICA: IF YOU GO 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 c.1999 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Getting there: A number of airlines, including American and Air
Jamaica, serve Montego Bay and Kingston with direct flights from
Miami. Tour companies, such as Go-Go and Apple Vacations
(www.applevacations.com/caribbean/jamaica), charter flights to the
island. See your travel agent.
</P>
<P>
   Resorts: Jamaica Grande Resort, Ocho Rios, Jamaica: 809-974-2201
or 800-HOTELS-1; on the Internet at www.renaissancehotels.com. The
resort has a Value Vacations package through Dec. 18 priced at $277
per person per day, double occupancy. Children under 12 stay and
eat free. The Weddings in Paradise package is $500.
</P>
<P>
   The Sunset Beach Resort &AMP; Spa, Montego Bay, Jamaica;
876-979-8800, www.sunsetbeachjamaica.com. Winter rates, Jan.
1-April 23, range from $240 to $380 per room per night, based on
double occupancy. Children are $35 per child per night.
</P>
<P>
   Insider's Jamaica is a program launched this year by the Jamaica
Tourism Board combining a five-night stay in a small hotel with
Jamaican sight-seeing. The 58 hotels in the program range from
mountain hideaways to family-run beachside inns and tropical
villas. Rates are $459 per person through Dec. 16. On the Web at
www.insidersjamaica.com
</P>
<P>
   Upcoming events: Jamerican Film &AMP; Music Festival, Nov. 17-21,
Montego Bay. Bob Marley All-Star Tribute, Dec. 4, at Island
Outpost's Oracabessa Bay.
</P>
<P>
   For more information: 800-JAMAICA (526-2422). On the Web at
www.jamaicatravel.com.
</P>
</TEXT>
