share. By Saul Hansell.
</P>
<P>
   BRAZIL-TELECOM (Sao Paulo) _ Brazil threatens to re-nationalize
the Embratel long-distance company that was sold to MCI Worldcom
unless MCI pays $700 million in back taxes. The threat illustrates
the continued unpredictability foreign companies confront in the
Government's meandering privatization effort. By Simon Romero.
</P>
