<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIDEO-SPOTLIGHT28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Spotlight on Tim Robbins (``Arlington Road'')
 &HT;    By Steve Murray
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Bull Durham'' (1988; R). Getting some sexy baseball training
from Susan Sarandon.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Jacob's Ladder'' (1990; R). Hallucinating some weird things
as a Vietnam vet in Adrian Lyne's horror flick.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Bob Roberts'' (1992; R). Running for president in this
satire (which he also wrote and directed).
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Player'' (1992; R). Getting in and out of trouble as the
ultimate Hollywood insider in Robert Altman's show-biz spoof.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Shawshank Redemption'' (1994; R). Finding friendship
behind bars with Morgan Freeman.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``The Hudsucker Proxy'' (1994; PG). Inventing the hula hoop in
the Coen Brothers' corporate comedy.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  ``Dead Man Walking'' (1995; R). He's not in it, but he
directed companion Sarandon to a best actress Oscar win.
</P>
<P>
   NOTABLE VIDEOS NOW ON SALE
</P>
<P>
   Silent classic: ``The Passion of Joan of Arc,'' Carl Dreyer's
masterpiece; $29.95 VHS, $39.95 DVD.
</P>
<P>
   Family: ``Muppets From Space,'' $21.95 VHS, $24.95 DV .
</P>
<P>
   DVD: ``The Taming of the Shrew'' (with Elizabeth Taylor and
Richard Burton), $27.95. ``Lilies,'' $24.95. ``Piranha: Special
Edition,'' including mini-feature on the making of the movie, audio
commentary from director Joe Dante and producer Jon Davison,
bloopers and outtakes, $24.98.
</P>
<P>
   _Steve Murray writes for the Atllanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
