<HEADLINE>
BRIMMING WITH ANSWERS ABOUT HAT ETIQUETTE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I'm a teacher and want to give a good reason for students to
remove hats when coming into school. What's the story behind this
rule of etiquette for men? _ S.M., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ The tradition is credited to King John of England, who
ruled from 1199 to 1216 and is better known for agreeing to the
Magna Carta. ``Kings expected people around them to show respect by
uncovering their heads when the monarch was in their midst,'' said
Jean Mitchell, a hat historian and owner of the Hattitudes shop in
Essex, Conn.
</P>
<P>
   The general rule has been that men should remove their hats when
indoors and women should keep them on unless the hat is considered
male attire _ such as a baseball cap. Today, many people at
weddings and other formal occasions keep their hats on, Mitchell
said.
</P>
<P>
   ``With today's gender equality, some of those rules are becoming
passe,'' she said. ``People wear western hats and baseball caps and
leave them on all the time.''
</P>
<P>
   To ask Mitchell a question about hat etiquette, call Hattitudes
at (860) 767-0775 or visit the Web site www.hattitudes.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Where can I find a Morris Minor club in the area? _
L.C., Fort Worth, texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ There doesn't appear to be a club in Fort Worth-Dallas,
but you can find 750 North American owners and enthusiasts of the
British car in the Morris Minor Registry.
</P>
<P>
   The club publishes a bimonthly newsletter with tips, meet
reports and other features. Membership dues are $20 per year.
</P>
<P>
   For more information, write to Morris Minor Registry, 318
Hampton Park, Westerville, OH 43081-5723, or visit the Web site
hometown.aol.com/morrisminr/page.
</P>
<P>
   The Morris Minor, which is sometimes confused with a Volkswagen
Beetle, was billed as the ``world's supreme small car'' at its
launch. More than 1.6 million were produced from 1948 to 1971.
</P>
<P>
   The Morris Minor Owners Club, a British group, publishes an
extensive Web site at www.morrisminoroc.co.uk.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ I know that the Walt Disney movie ``The Love Bug'' had
several sequels. What were they, and when did they come out? _
K.R.P., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ There were three sequels to the 1969 film ``The Love
Bug:'' ``Herbie Rides Again'' in 1974, ``Herbie Goes to Monte
Carlo'' in 1977 and ``Herbie Goes Bananas'' in 1980. All four are
available on video from Disney.
</P>
<P>
   There also was a 1982 TV series called ``Herbie, the Love Bug''
and a 1997 made-for-TV remake of the original movie titled ``The
Love Bug.''
</P>
<P>
   Dean Jones portrayed driver Jim Douglas in four of those
projects: both ``Love Bug'' movies, the TV series and ``Monte
Carlo.''  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL; 
 &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
