<P>
   MIT-GRANT (Cambridge, Mass.) _ &UR;  &LR; The chairman of ETrade makes a
$25 million grant to MIT's Sloan School of Business. By Steve
Wilmsen. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   BIOTECH-DRUGS (Undated) _ The world's largest pharmaceutical
company, HoechstMarianRoussel, is establishing a biotechnology
presence in Cambridge, Mass., spending $100 million to acquire the
rights to drugs under development by Ariad Pharmaceuticals. By
Ronald Rosenberg. &UR;  &LR; 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BKC-BIGEAST (Undated) _ Same story, different season. That's
what the Big East coaches predict will happen this basketball
season as they overwhelmingly select defending national champion
UConn as their preseason favorite. By Mark Blaudschun.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-BC (Undated) _ Syracuse might have an insight into what it
means to suffer a devastating loss after absorbing a humiliating
62-0 thrashing two weeks ago at Virginia Tech. But senior free
safety Pedro Cirino does not expect the Orangemen _ who host Boston
College in a Big East game Saturday _ to have any sympathy for the
Eagles after they squandered a 28-0 lead in a 31-28 loss last
Saturday against Miami. By Michael Vega
</P>
<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS (Foxborough, Mass.) -- Keyshawn Johnson is known
for his book, ``Just Give Me The Damn Ball!'' Maybe Drew Bledsoe's
autobiography should be titled ``Just Get Rid Of The Damn Ball!''
By Nick Cafardo.
