<P>
   DEATH-CONGRESS (Washington) _ Alarmed by an Oregon law that
allows doctors to help terminally ill patients end their lives, the
House is expected to pass legislation that will outlaw the
practice. There is support in the Senate for such a measure, and
the White House has signaled it may support such a step. By Robert
Pear.
