   DEMS-DEBATE (Undated) _ Democratic candidates Vice President Al
Gore and former Sen. Bill Bradley face off in New Hampshire in the
first of a half dozen debates that will be held over the next few
months. By Richard L. Berke.
</P>
<P>
   REPUBS-SOCSEC (Washington) _ Earl Pomeroy, D-N.D., has been one
of his party's strongest voices for protecting Social Security. So
he finds it particularly galling that he is one of seven Democrats
under attack in a Republican ad campaign that accuses the Democrats
in the House of raiding Social Security. He complains that a year
before the election, things are already on a campaign footing. And
that is just the point. After years of being clobbered by Democrats
in the annual budget fight, Republicans are aggressively aiming at
the next election, and seem to battling the Democrats to a draw. By
Alison Mitchell.
</P>
