   KIDNAP _ A kidnapper hid John LeBeau's infant twins somewhere in
Europe three years ago. To get them back, the Palm Beach Gardens
businessman traveled 30,000 miles on six trips overseas, hired
lawyers and investigators in three countries, learned international
law himself, badgered incessantly the U.S. government for help,
spent at least $150,000, and ultimately, with no small amount of
luck, found the children living in Britain with their abductor.
(Moffett, Palm Beach Post).
