<HEADLINE>
COACHES LIKE UCONN AGAIN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Same story, different season.
</P>
<P>
   That's what the Big East coaches predict will happen this
basketball season as they overwhelmingly selected the defending
national champion UConn Huskies as their preseason favorite, while
they predicted Boston College would finish in 13th and last place.
</P>
<P>
   UConn received 10 first place votes, while Syracuse (2) and
Miami (1) received the other first place votes.
</P>
<P>
   The coaches also predicted that UConn guard Khalid El-Amin as
Preseason Big East Player of the Year 6-11 Husky sophomore Ajou
Deng as preseason Rookie of The Year.
</P>
