<SLUG> BC-BELLSOUTH-GUATEMALA28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    BellSouth buys license for Guatemala wireless
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ BellSouth has continued its march through Latin
America, buying a $26 million license Wednesday to provide wireless
phone service in Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
   The license will extend BellSouth's presence to 14 countries
outside the United States, including 10 in Latin America and three
in Central America.
</P>
<P>
   Although Guatemala is relatively small _ with a population of 11
million _ it represents another link in a chain of BellSouth
investments that now reach from Guatemala's border with Mexico as
far south as Argentina and Chile.
</P>
<P>
   International business is, with wireless and local service in
the United States, a leg in BellSouth's strategic tripod. During
the past quarter, international operations reported revenue of $749
million, mostly from Latin America.
</P>
<P>
   BellSouth, whose local partners own 40 percent of the venture,
aims to have its Guatemalan service running next year, said
spokesman Kevin Doyle. BellSouth will have three competitors in
Guatemala, including the national company and a venture dominated
by Telefonica de Esapana.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
