   (NYT35) NEW YORK -- Oct. 27, 1999 -- BBO-WORLDSERIES-5, 10-27 --
Roger Clemens of the New York Yankees reacts after retiring the
first three Atlanta Braves batters to end the first inning of Game
4 of the World Series on Wednesday night. The Yankees lead the
best-of-seven series with the Atlanta Braves 3-0, and can clinch
their third title in 4 years with a victory. (Barton Silverman/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) NEW YORK -- Oct. 27, 1999 -- BBO-WORLDSERIES-4, 10-27 --
Roger Clemens of the New York Yankees on the mound during the first
inning of Game 4 of the World Series on Wednesday night. The
Yankees lead the best-of-seven series with the Atlanta Braves 3-0,
and can clinch their third title in 4 years with a victory. (Barton
Silverman/New York Times Photo)
