<SLUG> BC-FBN-COWBOYS-NOTES-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THOMAS NOW STARTING AT FULLBACK FOR COWBOYS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Rarely does lightning strike twice in the same
spot.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas Cowboys fullback Robert Thomas would beg to differ.
</P>
<P>
   Roughly two months after being hit with the news that the
Cowboys were going to move him from linebacker to fullback, Thomas
walked into the team's Valley Ranch headquarters Wednesday and was
overwhelmed again.
</P>
<P>
   The release of Tim Lester on Tuesday meant that Thomas, in his
second-year in the league and eighth week as a fullback, was going
to join the future Hall of Fame backfield of quarterback Troy
Aikman and running back Emmitt Smith as the starting fullback.
</P>
<P>
   ``It all just hit me,'' Thomas said. ``I found out when I came
in. It's a surprise. They told me it's my job to lose now. They
said I earned it. I'm happy, but I know I've still got work to do.
I've still got to get better.''
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coach Chan Gailey said Thomas had progressed enough
since switching positions near the end of training camp for them to
make the move with Lester.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he's been very good,'' said former starter and
resident fullback teacher Daryl Johnston, who is out for the season
with a neck injury.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's very impressive what he's done in such little time at the
position. He has a lot of potential. I don't see him having any
problems.''
</P>
<P>
   While the eight-year veteran Lester still understands the
nuances of fullback better than Thomas, Thomas has more explosion
as a blocker and comes at a cheaper salary. Lester was also a
liability on special teams.
</P>
<P>
   Another consideration is that the role of the fullback is not
the same as it was in the past. The Cowboys will use running back
Chris Warren as a fullback in the backfield with Smith a lot more.
They also will work more out of the one-back set with tight ends
Mike Lucky and David LaFleur taking the blocking assignments of the
fullback.
</P>
<P>
   Yet, the fullback position remains important _ to the team and
Smith personally.
</P>
<P>
   ``He needs to spend time with Daryl Johnston and myself and
learn what made him good and what made us click,'' Smith said. ``If
he doesn't do that, he's selling himself short and he's selling me
short and he's selling the team short.''
</P>
<P>
   Smith, however, is confident that the 6-foot-1, 255-pound Thomas
will measure up because he's a quick learner who has leaned heavily
on Johnston since the move in August.
</P>
<P>
   ``I wouldn't be where I am now without Moose,'' Thomas said.
``He has been a blessing to me, getting me ready physically and
mentally.''
</P>
<P>
   SMITH'S WORKLOAD
</P>
<P>
   Emmitt Smith, who has already carried the ball more times in his
career than any other running back in NFL history outside of Walter
Payton, is on pace for more attempts this season than ever before.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, 30, is averaging 25 rushes a game and would finish 1999
with 400 at the current pace. His previous high-tote mark was 377
in 1995. Only three running backs in NFL history have carried the
ball 400 times. Nobody has done that this late in a career.
</P>
<P>
   Even though it seemingly contradicts the
lessen-the-load-on-Smith mantra Chan Gailey came in with a year
ago, the Cowboys coach is not worried about Smith's carries.
</P>
<P>
   ``I never said anything about limiting Emmitt's carries,''
Gailey said. ``I've always said we wanted to give Emmitt some rest.
We've been able to do that on passing downs.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition to the rest Smith gets with backup Chris Warren
serving as the third-down back, Gailey said Smith takes less licks
because he doesn't pass-block. BRIEFLY
</P>
<P>
   _ Safety George Teague, who missed last week's game against the
Redskins, will be out one to three weeks with a herniated disk.
Izell Reese will start in his place against the Colts.
</P>
<P>
   _ Cornerback Kevin Mathis (hamstring) and center Mark Stepnoski
(low back contusion) missed practice Wednesday. Stepnoski is
expected to practice today and be ready for the Colts game. Mathis
is questionable for the Colts game.
</P>
<P>
   _ Receiver Wane McGarity (separated right shoulder) said it will
likely be another couple of weeks before it's decided when he'll
get back on the field. What's certain is that he'll probably need
surgery in the off-season to fully repair the shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   _ The Cowboys cut offensive lineman Ben Fricke and re-signed him
to the practice squad. They used the roster opening to sign rookie
free-agent safety Chris Akins off the Green Bay Packers' practice
squad. He will help out in the secondary and play special teams. nn
</P>
</TEXT>
