<SLUG> BC-STEINBERG-SPORTSAGENT-BUYOUY-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 LEIGH STEINBERG SELLS SPORTS AGENCY  &HT;     By DAVID LAZARUS 
 &HT;     c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
Steve Young was traded to Canada on Wednesday.
<P>
   OK, not exactly. But Young's high-profile sports agent, Leigh
Steinberg, did sell his privately held agency to a Canadian
financial management firm called Assante Corp.
</P>
<P>
   Terms of the acquisition were not disclosed. However, a source
close to the deal said Steinberg Moorad &AMP; Dunn fetched about $120
million and that Steinberg walked away with ``over half'' of that
amount.
</P>
<P>
   Steinberg now will serve as chief executive of Assante Sports
Management Group, the company's newly created subsidiary for
athletes. It will be based in both Berkeley, Calif., and Newport
Beach, Calif., and it will absorb all of Steinberg's 30 employees
and existing operations.
</P>
<P>
   Assante, which went public in Canada earlier this year,
describes itself as a ``wealth and life management firm.'' What
that means, according to Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
Martin Weinberg, is that Assante aims to handle all financial, tax,
insurance and business matters for its clients _ for life.
</P>
<P>
   Its show-biz clients include actors Tom Cruise and Michael J.
Fox and talk-show host David Letterman.
</P>
<P>
   Assante, which recently acquired two Los Angeles talent
agencies, wants to manage not just clients' money, but also their
careers.
</P>
<P>
   In deciding to branch out into sports, Weinberg said Assante
looked at more than a dozen agencies before settling on Steinberg
Moorad &AMP; Dunn. He described the acquisition as ``the perfect
marriage'' of sports and entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   Steinberg agreed, saying he expects all sorts of new marketing
opportunities to emerge from the deal. ``This will allow our
athletes access to new avenues and careers,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Such opportunities may be coming none too soon for Young, who
has suffered no fewer than four concussions in the past three years
and may sit out the remainder of this season.
</P>
<P>
   Steinberg enjoys considerable stature among sports agents. Among
other claims to fame, he said the film ``Jerry Maguire'' was
``loosely based'' on his own experiences.
</P>
<P>
   Other Steinberg clients include Dallas Cowboys quarterback Troy
Aikman, New England Patriots quarterback Drew Bledsoe and Arizona
Diamondbacks third baseman Matt Williams.
</P>
<P>
   Assante has more than 2,500 employees in 150 offices across
North America. It administers $17 billion in assets.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're the largest nonbank financial advisory firm in Canada,''
Weinberg said.
</P>
<P>
   In August, Assante reported quarterly revenue of $50 million, up
45 percent from a year earlier. But the company said recent
acquisitions had caused it to post a quarterly loss of $748,000,
compared with profit of $3.2 million a year before.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  Steinberg said Assante will now seek as many as a dozen other
sports agencies for additional acquisitions.
</P>
<P>
   ``We will have the largest collection of sports talent in the
world,'' he declared.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
